    "body": "It's not really about me, per se - I don't personally install anything with pip/trust software delivered by pip to be legitimate but that's kind of beside the point.  If py-evm is going to be included in debian, either py-evm will have to support 2.5 or debian will have to upgrade to 2.6.  py-evm is probably easier to regression test/etc against 2.5 than debian to 2.6(even though that should happen at some point too)",
