    "created_at": "2018-01-22T18:28:18Z",
    "updated_at": "2018-01-22T18:28:18Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I'm still not sure that I follow.\r\n\r\n- `py-evm` is usable without `tox`\r\n- development of `py-evm` does not **require** `tox`, but rather tox is used to make running the test suite across multiple python versions easier.\r\n\r\nI'm still failing to understand why a compatible version of `tox` is required for debian packaging.  I'm not inclined to pin ourselves to an old version of `tox` just for the possible eventuality that some other maintainer needs to be able to develop on a debian environment without use of `pip`.",
